{
  "date": "2026-02-06",
  "title": "Strength That Listens",
  "scriptures": [
    {
      "ref": "James 1:19",
      "text": "Wherefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow to wrath:"
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "key": "read_this_out_loud",
      "label": "Read This Out Loud",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Quick words are not always strong words."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Real strength is steady enough to listen."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I do not need to rush to prove myself."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I can slow down and hear clearly."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_devotional",
      "label": "The Devotional",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "There is a kind of power that only knows how to press forward."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It speaks fast."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Assumes quickly."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Reacts before it understands."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Scripture points us toward a different kind of strength."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "One that is grounded enough to hear first."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Listening is not weakness."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It is often the discipline that keeps truth from turning into noise."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "When a person slows down long enough to hear, they make room for wisdom, patience, and mercy."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_shift",
      "label": "The Shift",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Many conflicts are fueled less by evil and more by speed."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Fast assumptions.",
            "Fast responses.",
            "Fast anger."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "James gives a better rhythm."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Swift to hear.",
            "Slow to speak.",
            "Slow to wrath."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Wisdom often enters where hurry leaves."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "jesus_set_the_pattern",
      "label": "Jesus Set the Pattern",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Jesus was never controlled by urgency."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He could hear people fully."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He asked questions."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He answered with clarity, not panic."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He was never in a rush to prove His authority."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He carried it quietly."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Where have I been too quick to speak?",
            "What would change if I listened longer before reacting?",
            "Who in my life may need to feel heard, not handled?"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "declaration",
      "label": "Declaration",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will not be ruled by hurry."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will listen with patience."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will let wisdom slow my words and steady my reactions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "action_step",
      "label": "Action Step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "In your next meaningful conversation, practice restraint."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Let the other person finish.",
            "Ask one more question before responding.",
            "Pause before you answer."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Choose strength that listens."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "one_sentence_to_carry",
      "label": "One Sentence to Carry",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "text": "Strength does not rush; it listens."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "__insert_block_header": "2026-02-06_james-1-19_strength-that-listens|"
}
